The paper discusses the development of an anytime optimal algorithm for action selection in MDPs, which involves exploring and exploiting the search space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of non-admissible heuristics and random sampling of policies suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of dynamic programming algorithms and the exploration-exploitation tradeoff suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the development of an optimal policy suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
